  "prompt": "Are there specific laws targeting money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, many countries have specific anti-money laundering (AML) laws and regulations. In the United States, key laws include the Bank Secrecy Act and the USA PATRIOT Act. These laws require financial institutions to:\n\n1. Implement customer identification programs\n2. Report suspicious transactions\n3. Maintain transaction records\n4. Conduct due diligence on customers\n5. Screen for potential money laundering activities\n\nPenalties for money laundering can include significant fines and criminal prosecution. International organizations like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) also provide global standards for combating money laundering.",
